notes_display: Medal commemorates the Capture of Ghent and Bruges.  It is composed of white metal with a copper plug.
issue_obverse_figure_description_s: Duke of Marlborough and Prince Eugene represented each holding a laurel-wreath and plucking a flower from a lily.  Meant to represent recent victory at Oudernarde and the capture of yet another French possession.
issue_obverse_legend_s: AD EXORNANDAM LAVREAM . | EVGENII ET MARLBORVGII | CONIVNCTIO GALLORVM | DISSIPATIO .
issue_reverse_figure_description_s: Depiction of a boy catching a cock with a hook and line, meant to represent the bait left out for the French in their taking of Ghent and Bruges without resistance, ultimately leading to the English victory at the battle of Oudenarde.
issue_reverse_legend_s: VÆ TIBI LVDENTI NAM MOX POST IVBILA FLEBIS . | GALLI GANDAVO ET BRVGA CAP- | TA , ALDENARDAM OBSES- | SVRI VINCVNTVR . | MDCCIIX . XI . IVL .
